This is, uh, a poem that was...

00:37.805 --> 00:40.806
uh, I found it in the library.

00:40.808 --> 00:42.775
It's for my son.

00:44.578 --> 00:47.146
"To a child dancing in the wind.

00:49.617 --> 00:52.651
"Dance there upon the shore.

00:52.653 --> 00:54.586
"What need have you to care...

00:54.588 --> 00:56.588
"For wind or waters roar?

00:56.590 --> 00:59.324
"Tumble out your hair.

00:59.326 --> 01:01.160
"That the salt drops have wet;

01:03.364 --> 01:07.066
"What need have you to dread the
monstrous crying of the wind?"

01:50.478 --> 01:52.878
Excuse me. Excuse me.
Excuse me.

02:14.268 --> 02:16.869
Excuse me.

02:16.871 --> 02:19.304
James? James?

02:19.306 --> 02:21.140
James! James! Come here.

02:22.643 --> 02:25.144
Stay close, okay?

02:25.146 --> 02:27.312
Give me your hand. Tight.
Hold it tight.

02:38.259 --> 02:40.159
Sorry. Sorry.

02:42.363 --> 02:43.924
I'm sorry. Where are they?

02:57.211 --> 02:59.745
Listen, frank. You look after yourself.
All right?

02:59.747 --> 03:02.181
Angela, this way.

03:02.183 --> 03:04.344
Sorry. Excuse me.

03:05.853 --> 03:07.920
There she goes, boys.

03:15.329 --> 03:17.462
Look at that.
Is that fantastic?

03:23.270 --> 03:25.804
Rob! Mum. There you are.

03:25.806 --> 03:28.307
- Hello.
- Thought I was going to Miss it.

03:30.978 --> 03:33.278
Where's grandpa? I don't know.

03:40.321 --> 03:42.721
Pappy won't be coming.
He's not here.

03:59.974 --> 04:01.940
Come on, frank.

04:07.681 --> 04:09.982
You're missing it, frank.

04:17.891 --> 04:20.851
You coming out? I'll be
out in a minute, danny.

04:34.875 --> 04:38.195
How can they let someone else build our navy ships?
It's just the way it is.

04:40.714 --> 04:43.649
And you?
How can they let you go?

04:45.919 --> 04:48.754
You want this? No, thanks.

05:10.711 --> 05:12.811
All right, gus?

05:17.484 --> 05:19.351
You all right?

05:43.744 --> 05:46.044
Joan redmond? Yeah. I'm sorry.

05:46.046 --> 05:48.647
Excuse me. Sorry.

05:48.649 --> 05:51.616
Excuse me. Sorry.

05:55.356 --> 05:58.056
Sorry. Right.

05:58.058 --> 06:01.893
As I was saying, driving a bus is
exactly the same as driving a car,

06:01.895 --> 06:05.097
except for the 50 or so backseat
drivers sitting behind you.

06:25.052 --> 06:27.819
Rob brought the boys
for your last day.

06:31.024 --> 06:33.725
They were looking for you.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.795
Gus fuller lost his hand today.

06:36.797 --> 06:40.832
Oh? How?

06:40.834 --> 06:42.734
One of the presses.

06:49.510 --> 06:51.109
Will he get more money?

06:53.514 --> 06:55.447
I watched him do it.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.134
That's you... tidy.

07:56.844 --> 07:58.710
See you soon, love.

08:22.035 --> 08:24.269
Hello. Hi.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.605
J.SA., pensions or disability?

08:26.607 --> 08:28.707
I'm looking for a job.

08:28.709 --> 08:31.610
First time? Yeah.

08:31.612 --> 08:33.511
You'll need to speak
to someone.

08:33.514 --> 08:35.679
Let's see who's free.

08:52.266 --> 08:55.534
- Angela.
- All right?

08:55.536 --> 08:58.036
Okay.

09:20.093 --> 09:23.628
Look, frank, you don't have
to fill it in here.

09:23.630 --> 09:25.630
You can do it at home.

10:06.306 --> 10:09.174
Won't be the same at work
without frank.

10:09.176 --> 10:11.776
You got the boot as well,
you dozy pillock.

10:11.778 --> 10:14.346
He might have a heart attack.
That happens, doesn't it?

10:14.348 --> 10:16.748
Work monday, redundant tuesday,

10:16.750 --> 10:19.618
heart attack wednesday.

10:19.620 --> 10:23.254
Well, frank'll be all right then.
Today's thursday.

10:23.256 --> 10:26.625
What in the name of total
insanity are you wearing?

10:26.627 --> 10:29.628
Oh! I need clean ones.

10:29.630 --> 10:33.131
- Tell me they're not your mother's.
- Don't be daft.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.800
They're big janine's. She left
'em in the pub again on friday.

10:35.802 --> 10:39.037
- Don't let frank catch you wearing 'em.
- I knew they'd come in handy.

10:39.039 --> 10:41.906
- For what, exactly?
- What if I get run over?

10:44.711 --> 10:47.712
Frank won't be coming
swimming tonight.

10:47.714 --> 10:50.181
I'm glad I got out of there when I did.
It's turned nasty.

10:50.183 --> 10:52.751
Frank could have stayed on like I did.
The men respect him.

10:52.753 --> 10:56.154
All he had to do was let them upstairs
think they were runnin' the job.

10:56.156 --> 10:58.289
Man's too pigheaded
for his own good.

11:06.366 --> 11:08.607
- Frank, I didn't mean...
- Leave it, eddie.

11:17.444 --> 11:19.911
See you in the pool then.

12:10.097 --> 12:11.996
Frank?

12:16.203 --> 12:18.403
Frank?

12:20.307 --> 12:24.109
- Frank?
- Frank?

12:24.111 --> 12:28.213
Frank, where are you going?

12:28.215 --> 12:30.415
- Frank.
- - Oh, my god.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.383
Here, man. Here.

12:34.888 --> 12:38.523
- Get an ambulance, joan. Get an ambulance.
- Please, no!

12:38.525 --> 12:41.805
- You're all right, man. You're all right.
- Get out of my way!

12:47.534 --> 12:50.301
It's okay. He's okay.
Dad's fine.

12:50.303 --> 12:53.037
It was a panic attack.
That's what the doctor said.

12:53.039 --> 12:55.340
What? A panic attack.

12:55.342 --> 12:57.509
Only don't mention it
when he comes out.

12:57.511 --> 13:00.011
Okay, let's go.

13:00.013 --> 13:02.113
Eddie rang me.
Eddie's got a big mouth.

13:02.115 --> 13:04.849
- He was worried.
- I slipped, okay?

13:04.851 --> 13:07.218
- Can I get money for a can of coke?
- You collapsed.

13:07.220 --> 13:09.087
No, we're not allowed. -Mum
says you had a panic attack.

13:09.089 --> 13:11.289
I slipped and fell.
It happens, okay?

13:11.291 --> 13:13.925
What are you asking for? Sorry. -Have
you got money for a can of coke?

13:13.927 --> 13:16.427
No. No. I don't have any money.

13:16.429 --> 13:18.963
Do you have your purse?
No, I don't have my purse.

13:18.965 --> 13:20.498
Right. Ask your dad for the money.
How do I get out of here?

13:20.500 --> 13:23.001
Down there. Where? Right, left?
Where?

13:23.003 --> 13:24.335
That way, frank. Right.
I'll find it.

13:24.337 --> 13:27.038
I'm sorry, love.

13:27.040 --> 13:29.841
Come on, boys, let's go.

13:29.843 --> 13:33.845
What's the matter with you?
You shouldn't...

13:33.847 --> 13:36.488
you could have said hello. You
should not have told him.

13:42.489 --> 13:44.255
Hands.

13:55.035 --> 13:56.601
Is pappy all right?

13:58.038 --> 13:59.871
Of course he is.

14:04.511 --> 14:07.879
Do you like pappy?

14:07.881 --> 14:09.961
Pappy and I are just different.

14:11.151 --> 14:12.951
Pappy doesn't like you.

14:25.599 --> 14:28.533
Oh, look who it is.
Frank's little girl.

14:32.339 --> 14:35.139
Got our fish suppers
ready yet, chinaman?

14:35.141 --> 14:39.944
Oh, god love us. He's a real
chatterbox tonight, isn't he?

14:42.549 --> 14:44.315
Tell you what...
I've changed my mind.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.351
I fancy a curry.

14:56.329 --> 14:57.929
See you tuesday.

15:05.906 --> 15:08.107
Just a bag of chips,
please, chan.

15:10.944 --> 15:14.445
Heard about your dad.
I'm, uh, sorry.

15:24.958 --> 15:29.060
Okay, chan? Frank. All right?

15:29.062 --> 15:31.462
Good book?

15:31.464 --> 15:34.699
It's for my wife.

15:34.701 --> 15:36.935
It's about cooking.

15:38.405 --> 15:40.638
What are you looking for?

15:42.575 --> 15:44.475
Don't know.

15:46.947 --> 15:49.180
But whatever it is,
it's not in here.

15:58.992 --> 16:01.292
He doesn't know what to do
with himself anymore.

16:01.294 --> 16:03.962
More than I can say for you, driving a bus.
Have you told him yet?

16:03.964 --> 16:06.631
No. Don't want to give him
anything else to worry about.

16:06.633 --> 16:09.701
He's gonna find out
sooner or later.

16:09.703 --> 16:13.004
He's shut me out again,
michelle, like when stuart...

16:13.006 --> 16:16.107
it won't last long. Are things
better with him and rob?

16:16.109 --> 16:18.309
Not really.

16:28.455 --> 16:30.288
Hey. Hiya.

16:30.290 --> 16:32.557
- Bag of chips, please.
- Okay.

16:36.429 --> 16:40.031
- Is your dad around?
- No.

16:40.033 --> 16:41.766
Salt and vinegar?

16:43.303 --> 16:45.203
Please.

17:03.256 --> 17:05.490
Oh! Hi, frank. Come on in.

17:05.492 --> 17:08.059
I'm just off to work.

17:08.060 --> 17:10.194
Tom cruise
is in the front room.

17:10.195 --> 17:12.763
Eddie, it's frank.
He's got chips.

17:21.241 --> 17:24.541
Our industrious little beetle
is about to meet someone...

17:24.544 --> 17:27.345
Altogether more...
I've seen this before.

17:27.347 --> 17:31.049
Let's call him...
that wee beetle...

17:31.051 --> 17:36.320
Pushes that big ball of shite for what
is the equivalent of six miles for him.

17:36.322 --> 17:38.322
Then, just as he gets
to where he's going,

17:39.559 --> 17:42.193
another beetle comes...

17:42.195 --> 17:44.495
And steals it
from under his nose.

17:44.497 --> 17:46.731
It's what happens.
Wait, you'll see.

17:46.733 --> 17:48.800
Six miles.

17:48.802 --> 17:51.202
Poor bastard.

17:51.204 --> 17:53.771
They'll have you shoveling shit.
You know that?

17:56.476 --> 17:57.196
I know.

18:02.182 --> 18:04.215
You still coming on the
booze cruise to france?

18:04.217 --> 18:06.751
It'll do us good.

18:06.753 --> 18:09.454
I can see myself
on the ship now...

18:09.456 --> 18:11.622
captain eddie fraser.

18:11.624 --> 18:17.361
Beer in hand, and the
sea air in my lungs.

18:17.363 --> 18:20.631
Oh, eddie, that seagull's
eating your puke.

18:23.103 --> 18:26.471
He caught it in the air. That
seagull caught it in the air.

18:26.473 --> 18:29.574
Puke again, eddie.
Go on, puke again.

18:33.246 --> 18:36.247
Brilliant, that.

18:52.132 --> 18:53.898
All right?

18:56.569 --> 18:59.837
Bloody hell.
You can see france already.

18:59.839 --> 19:01.739
Isn't very far, is it?

19:01.741 --> 19:04.208
Near enough to swim.

19:04.210 --> 19:06.210
I wish I had.

19:33.506 --> 19:35.339
Frank?

19:35.341 --> 19:37.375
Frank?

19:38.778 --> 19:40.811
You all right?

19:44.884 --> 19:47.451
How mad would you
have to be to swim this?

19:47.453 --> 19:49.554
Totally.

19:58.198 --> 20:02.333
How far is it to france? We're
in france, you dipstick.

20:02.335 --> 20:05.369
Yeah, I know we're in france,
but how far is it from britain?

20:05.371 --> 20:09.707
Twenty miles, give or take
the odd oil tanker.

20:09.709 --> 20:11.976
Twenty miles, eh?
How do they measure that?

20:11.978 --> 20:13.744
They look very small
from here, don't they?

20:13.746 --> 20:16.347
They are very small, love.

20:16.349 --> 20:18.583
It's just us women like to
shrink when we get near them.

20:18.585 --> 20:22.987
You can't swim across one of the busiest
shipping routes 'cause the fancy takes you.

20:22.989 --> 20:26.290
Who'd you show your passport to?
Punch and judy?

20:26.292 --> 20:29.760
The deck chair man. -I was
a deck chair man for a day.

20:29.762 --> 20:34.532
- Only a day?
- Wasn't what I was expecting.

20:34.534 --> 20:38.803
Did you tell him? No. God, no.

20:38.805 --> 20:42.974
I will. He won't like it. He'll think
it's to do with him losing his job.

20:42.976 --> 20:45.910
And he'll like it even less
when he finds out the truth...

20:47.981 --> 20:51.301
that it's got absolutely
nothing to do with him at all.

21:08.835 --> 21:11.002
Sorry to pull you back
to the yard like this, frank.

21:11.004 --> 21:13.838
It's a small, little matter.
I just need to prove something.

21:13.840 --> 21:16.407
I know you must be busy.

21:17.910 --> 21:19.844
You know these guys, frank.

21:21.347 --> 21:23.581
So? I've told you...

21:23.583 --> 21:26.484
I didn't see anything.

21:26.486 --> 21:28.519
He must have been desperate.

21:28.521 --> 21:30.888
He's going to get nothing.

21:30.890 --> 21:33.424
He used the wrong hand.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.560
He's right-handed.

21:38.598 --> 21:40.464
Duncan?

21:42.835 --> 21:46.304
He crossed hands
to operate the press.

21:49.842 --> 21:51.809
Okay.

21:55.682 --> 21:58.883
You should have been more
loyal to the company, frank.

21:58.885 --> 22:01.952
You wouldn't know
what loyalty is.

22:01.954 --> 22:04.488
Loyalty is a full wage packet
at the end of the week.

22:05.792 --> 22:09.060
Loyalty is being valued.

22:09.062 --> 22:11.062
Being happy with yourself.

22:12.665 --> 22:14.532
You happy with yourself, frank?

22:16.836 --> 22:20.538
Who do you think you are?

22:20.540 --> 22:24.542
You seriously think you can intimidate
people into being loyal to you?

22:26.979 --> 22:30.014
There's not a man in this yard would
piss on you if you were on fire.

22:38.458 --> 22:41.092
Hi, frank. Can't keep away, eh?

23:51.197 --> 23:53.998
I knocked a vase over.
Which one?

23:54.000 --> 23:55.966
The one with the crack in it?

23:55.968 --> 23:57.802
No, the other one.

23:59.572 --> 24:01.439
Will it fix?

24:07.213 --> 24:09.547
I need to go and get changed.

24:16.522 --> 24:19.123
So what if you swam the clyde?
It doesn't prove anything.

24:19.125 --> 24:21.091
Channel's a completely
different thing.

24:21.093 --> 24:23.594
Think you could then, frank?

24:23.596 --> 24:25.529
- I know I could.
- Look.

24:25.531 --> 24:27.832
You got made redundant.

24:27.834 --> 24:30.000
You should just face up to it,
like everyone else.

24:44.951 --> 24:47.084
Face up to it?

24:52.525 --> 24:54.124
Like you did, eddie?

25:15.548 --> 25:18.782
That's a lot of reading.
That's a lot of swimming.

25:18.784 --> 25:20.985
You think I'm wasting my time?

25:20.987 --> 25:23.087
"A gem cannot be polished
without friction,

25:23.089 --> 25:25.789
nor a man perfected
without trials."

25:27.660 --> 25:30.094
Is that a yes or a no?

25:30.096 --> 25:31.896
When do we start?

25:51.951 --> 25:54.184
Hey, hey, hey.

25:54.186 --> 25:56.687
What have we forgotten?

25:59.859 --> 26:03.060
What's this?

26:03.062 --> 26:05.829
You know you're not allowed.
In you go.

26:05.831 --> 26:08.766
I'll see you at 3:30.

26:08.768 --> 26:10.267
Bye. Bye!

26:22.882 --> 26:26.584
- Hiya, son.
- Dad.

26:26.586 --> 26:28.886
Okay?

26:28.888 --> 26:31.589
You?

26:31.591 --> 26:35.092
- Yeah, good.
- Busy?

26:35.094 --> 26:37.628
Aye.

26:40.900 --> 26:43.767
You used to have one of them.
Remember?

26:43.769 --> 26:46.136
Yeah.

26:46.138 --> 26:48.178
They had one each,
but they're always losing them.

26:51.644 --> 26:54.712
I was going to go for a coffee.
Wanna come?

26:54.714 --> 26:58.782
I'd better not. Got to get on.
Maybe next time.

27:01.087 --> 27:03.087
Aye.

27:22.208 --> 27:25.075
Promised michelle
I'd fix this for her.

27:25.077 --> 27:27.711
Just wanted to see
what was inside.

27:27.713 --> 27:30.047
Now it doesn't seem to want
to go back together.

27:30.049 --> 27:33.017
Things aren't meant
to be fixed nowadays.

27:33.019 --> 27:35.285
No.

27:36.689 --> 27:38.322
Not by you anyway.

27:44.397 --> 27:46.330
How's work?

27:51.070 --> 27:54.672
What was it sausage finger said today?
Something funny.

27:59.679 --> 28:02.379
No, I can't remember. It was
funny anyway, whatever it was.

28:02.381 --> 28:05.716
The thing that he said,
it was funny.

28:07.920 --> 28:09.687
I'm gonna swim it, ed.

28:13.826 --> 28:15.793
I know you are.

28:38.017 --> 28:41.051
Oh, my, that's a lot of reading.
It's a lot of swimming.

28:41.053 --> 28:44.254
Probably mentions sharks.
Does it mention sharks, frank?

28:44.256 --> 28:47.157
- There's no sharks in the channel.
- This one shark...

28:47.159 --> 28:49.893
when they opened it up, they found a
portable telly and a box of condoms.

28:49.895 --> 28:52.229
- They did not.
- Don't tell me the telly was still on.

28:52.231 --> 28:55.265
Look. It's important they take
this seriously and do it properly,

28:55.267 --> 28:57.868
or you may as well not bother.

28:57.870 --> 28:59.737
Bloody hell. Bugger me.

28:59.739 --> 29:02.773
Are you coming,
or are you going?

29:02.775 --> 29:06.310
Sorry, frank.

29:06.312 --> 29:09.780
To start with,
there's the training schedule.

29:09.782 --> 29:12.916
I don't mean to be rude, chan... -A list
of things we need to do to set the swim up.

29:12.918 --> 29:16.019
But I didn't think you could speak english.
I didn't think you could speak.

29:16.021 --> 29:20.290
Danny. First, we need
to register the swim.

29:20.292 --> 29:23.894
I've only ever heard you say about three words,
and two of them were "salt" and "vinegar."

29:23.896 --> 29:27.131
For the love of god,
will you let the man speak?

29:27.133 --> 29:31.101
Sorry, chan. Next we have to get
a boat and an experienced pilot.

29:31.103 --> 29:33.971
How about merv?
He's got a boat.

29:33.973 --> 29:36.507
Merv the perv's got a boat?

29:36.509 --> 29:39.309
It's one of them daft, pointy ones.
It's all chrome and shiny plastic.

29:39.311 --> 29:42.079
No, I don't want to talk to merv.
It's got a dinky, wee bar.

29:42.081 --> 29:44.401
Does it go fast though?
Like shit off a stick.

30:00.866 --> 30:03.100
Two years...
that's what it takes.

30:03.102 --> 30:06.470
I want to do it in six months.

30:06.472 --> 30:08.071
Will you have time to help me?

30:08.073 --> 30:10.974
Aye.

30:13.512 --> 30:16.213
Ed, I would have asked you, but I
didn't think you would have the time.

30:16.215 --> 30:19.016
Aye. Well...

30:19.018 --> 30:22.219
chan is probably better at this
sort of thing than me anyway.

30:27.226 --> 30:30.227
Look, guys, uh... do me a favor, and
can we just keep this to ourselves?

30:30.229 --> 30:32.596
Sure. Aye.

30:34.366 --> 30:37.901
Is he in? Aye. He's
in the kitchen.

30:37.903 --> 30:40.003
Right.

30:45.244 --> 30:47.684
Good evening, joan.
Hello, norman.

30:50.382 --> 30:53.317
I've got a cake. Oh. Very nice.

30:59.258 --> 31:02.159
Hello, Mrs. Redmond. Hello.

31:02.161 --> 31:05.929
It's danny. Danny campbell.
Ah. Right.

31:05.931 --> 31:08.498
You want frank?
He's in the kitchen.

31:15.941 --> 31:18.308
Come in.

31:18.310 --> 31:20.210
He's in the kitchen.

32:27.446 --> 32:31.348
Keep your eyes open, james.
In here.

32:31.350 --> 32:34.618
On you go.

32:34.620 --> 32:37.321
All right, rob? Hey, danny.
How's things?

32:37.323 --> 32:40.190
Aw, not bad. Skint.
No job, no girlfriend.

32:40.192 --> 32:43.126
And I've been wearing big janine's
knickers since last february.

32:43.128 --> 32:45.696
I can't complain.
It's not easy, that...

32:45.698 --> 32:47.597
doing a woman's job.

32:47.599 --> 32:49.733
Here, I'll leave you to it.

32:49.735 --> 32:52.069
Rather you than me.

32:52.071 --> 32:54.404
You okay? Yeah.

32:54.406 --> 32:56.640
Leave it alone, you big numpty.

32:56.642 --> 33:00.444
And try to stay on your feet.

33:00.446 --> 33:04.181
I saw dad down the pool again.
What's he up to? Swimming.

33:04.183 --> 33:05.615
It seems he's there all the time.
It does him good.

33:05.617 --> 33:08.618
Away you go.

33:08.620 --> 33:11.154
How did they both manage
to fall over?

33:11.156 --> 33:14.091
Practice.

33:14.093 --> 33:16.226
Can we go up to our room?
Yes, you can.

33:16.228 --> 33:18.996
I didn't know you had this.

33:20.065 --> 33:23.266
Angela dug it out.

33:23.268 --> 33:26.436
It's a good sand boat.

33:26.438 --> 33:29.573
That's all you ever wanted to make, both of you.
Must be in your blood.

33:29.575 --> 33:31.475
Biscuit?

33:33.512 --> 33:36.279
- I go up there now and then.
- Hmm. I know.

33:50.229 --> 33:52.162
Mum?

33:55.401 --> 33:57.768
I failed my bus test.

34:04.510 --> 34:07.044
That's not bad.

34:07.046 --> 34:09.713
Time's faster and you're getting
more distance from the strokes.

34:09.715 --> 34:12.248
But it's still a long way
from the real thing.

34:15.286 --> 34:18.255
You'd be better
at bus driving than me.

34:18.257 --> 34:20.757
I thought about it.
Kept seeing those ads.

34:20.759 --> 34:23.326
So, why didn't you tell us?

34:25.697 --> 34:27.563
There's no sugar in this.

34:30.101 --> 34:33.136
Can you take it again?
You get three goes.

34:33.138 --> 34:36.473
You should try for it.
You'd be good.

34:36.475 --> 34:39.775
What, and have angela give up work?
She earns twice what I could.

34:39.777 --> 34:42.079
I've said before,
I can help with the twins.

34:42.081 --> 34:44.246
And I've said before,
they're my kids.

34:44.248 --> 34:47.089
If I'm not prepared to look after them,
then we shouldn't have had them.

34:48.454 --> 34:51.121
What? You're like your dad.

35:03.335 --> 35:05.836
You wait right here
at this side of the pool.

35:05.838 --> 35:08.705
Right, go beside campbell.

35:08.707 --> 35:11.308
Good boy.

35:11.310 --> 35:14.750
Aaron, when you get to the side
of the pool, just stop and wait.

35:15.614 --> 35:17.547
Whoop.

35:20.752 --> 35:22.586
Hold on, jonathan.

35:37.369 --> 35:39.870
- You okay? You okay?
- He's all right. He's all right.

35:39.872 --> 35:41.705
I'm all right. It's the way he swims.
It's okay.

35:41.707 --> 35:44.841
Just leave him.
Thank you. Thank you.

35:57.289 --> 35:59.589
Yes!

35:59.591 --> 36:02.792
- Yes!
- Did you see that, big man?

36:29.521 --> 36:31.555
You call that swimming?

36:31.557 --> 36:33.456
Aye.

36:37.429 --> 36:39.462
Have you got a name?

36:39.464 --> 36:41.498
Aaron.

36:43.202 --> 36:45.769
Good name.

36:45.771 --> 36:47.671
Good swimmer.

36:53.512 --> 36:55.445
Rob, hurry up.

37:07.659 --> 37:11.228
Come on, let's go.
He's probably not here.

37:11.230 --> 37:13.830
You said he comes down here all the time.
Unless you don't want to.

37:13.832 --> 37:15.799
No, I'm coming. And I didn't
say, "all of the time."

37:15.801 --> 37:17.934
I said, "some of the time,"
Smart-arse.

37:17.936 --> 37:19.936
Where are you going to?
All right, frank?

37:19.938 --> 37:22.472
All right, danny.

37:22.474 --> 37:24.755
Who's that?
I used to work with him.

37:40.492 --> 37:42.959
Okay. Okay.

37:50.836 --> 37:53.603
Who's gonna be first?
No cheating.

37:53.605 --> 37:56.506
You got a head start.

37:56.508 --> 37:58.441
Ah, my toe. I stubbed my toe.

37:58.443 --> 38:00.510
Who won the race? You.

38:04.516 --> 38:06.583
- Whose clothes are who here?
- Anyone else in here?

38:06.585 --> 38:09.653
No, no. You're safe.

38:09.655 --> 38:11.856
Will you come out of there?
Why are you hiding in there?

38:11.857 --> 38:15.825
You've got the shampoo?
Oh, have I?

38:15.827 --> 38:19.396
Why do men's changing rooms always
smell of P-i-s-s? You're lucky.

38:19.398 --> 38:21.364
Normally they smell of S-h-i-t.

38:21.366 --> 38:23.500
What does that spell?

38:28.840 --> 38:30.740
All right, clothes on.
Who's first?

38:30.742 --> 38:32.842
Come on. Let's get dressed.
T-shirt.

38:32.844 --> 38:35.378
You're cold. You're freezing.

39:03.408 --> 39:05.642
See you monday.

39:05.644 --> 39:07.577
Excuse me.

39:10.449 --> 39:12.415
See you monday.

39:18.557 --> 39:20.690
Just the three. Danny.

39:22.861 --> 39:25.428
Get his change right, shirley.
He'll be watching the pennies.

39:59.831 --> 40:03.099
It's not even may. You can't go
swimming outdoors this time of year.

40:03.101 --> 40:05.935
I've got to get colder. I'm
going to loch lomond tomorrow.

40:05.937 --> 40:08.438
There's frost forecast tonight.

40:08.440 --> 40:10.573
I think we should all do it.
Lend a bit of morale.

40:10.575 --> 40:12.776
I'll do it. Sounds like a laugh.
What about you, eddie?

40:12.778 --> 40:15.812
Oh, yeah, yeah. Count me in. Not me.
I support much better when I'm dry.

40:15.814 --> 40:17.947
I'm more your dry kind of supporter.
Nice cake, norman.

40:17.949 --> 40:19.716
Yeah, less salt this time.

40:24.756 --> 40:27.424
Here we go!

40:32.564 --> 40:35.465
Oh, eddie, where are you going?

40:35.467 --> 40:37.467
No. Oh, no. Eddie, come on.

40:37.469 --> 40:39.536
No. Get off me.

40:42.574 --> 40:44.641
Oh! Oh! I've got piles!

40:49.514 --> 40:51.514
Hold on, frank!

40:51.516 --> 40:53.616
I'll be right with you!

40:58.523 --> 41:00.590
Don't worry, son.
It'll grow back.

41:00.592 --> 41:02.992
It better had.
I'm playing football later on.

41:02.994 --> 41:06.195
Here we go, lads. Nice
cold beers to warm you up.

41:07.098 --> 41:08.798
- Hey, salange.
- - Salange.

41:10.502 --> 41:13.002
The fire of the crucible.

41:13.004 --> 41:15.705
God. What is the "fire of the crucible"?
A chinese proverb.

41:15.707 --> 41:18.541
From now on you have to
train in the cold.

41:18.543 --> 41:21.511
Not only that, you have to swim
25 miles a week, six days a week.

41:21.513 --> 41:24.113
Here. I've got one
for you, chan.

41:24.115 --> 41:27.155
Man who walks through airport turnstile
sideways is going to bangkok.

41:33.492 --> 41:35.925
How do you know
he's going to bangkok?

41:35.927 --> 41:37.760
Bang cock.

41:37.762 --> 41:41.164
Bang cock.

41:41.166 --> 41:45.134
Listen. We still need
to get ahold of a boat...

41:45.136 --> 41:49.038
- so we can support frank in the water.
