- I don't see why not.

41:51.243 --> 41:53.610
He'd let you have a go
with his wife.

41:53.612 --> 41:56.079
Bang cock. Bang cock.

42:10.128 --> 42:12.262
Oh, no, I can't.

42:12.264 --> 42:14.564
I thought I could, but I can't.

42:14.566 --> 42:16.766
- I'll see you at the bus stop.
- Hey!

42:16.768 --> 42:19.302
Hey, over here. Come on.

42:22.274 --> 42:25.642
Don't be shy. Give it a try.

42:25.644 --> 42:27.710
Merv, it's frank.

42:27.712 --> 42:30.613
Can I have a word?

42:30.615 --> 42:34.083
Hiya, frank.
Hey, vera, it's frank.

42:34.085 --> 42:36.185
Hi, vera.

42:36.187 --> 42:40.757
How's joan? Joan's... she's... she's fine.
She's... yeah.

42:40.759 --> 42:44.093
She's still after joan's
recipe for lemon cheesecake.

42:44.095 --> 42:47.130
I'll remind her.

42:47.132 --> 42:50.266
Listen. I'm sorry.
Is this a bad time?

42:50.268 --> 42:53.708
- 'Cause, I mean, I could come back later.
- No, it's great, frank.

42:54.606 --> 42:56.739
Norman says you've got a boat.

42:56.741 --> 42:59.976
I was wondering
if maybe we could borrow it.

42:59.978 --> 43:02.779
I want to shag it!

43:02.781 --> 43:06.249
- Merv probably has.
- You sure you know what you're doing?

43:06.251 --> 43:09.819
Of course I do. I used
to be in the sea cadets.

43:09.821 --> 43:11.888
Bit different to a leaky canoe
on the clyde, this.

43:11.890 --> 43:14.624
Don't worry. I'll be careful.

43:14.626 --> 43:18.695
- Yeah, well, just make sure you are.
- Are you not coming, norman?

43:18.697 --> 43:22.298
Get on there with the missing link at the helm?
You're joking, aren't you?

43:22.300 --> 43:26.769
No. Uh, I'll leave it till I find my sea legs.
Next time maybe.

43:28.173 --> 43:31.007
Help! Slow down!

43:34.779 --> 43:36.613
Right then.

43:43.054 --> 43:46.356
- Aw, you flooded it.
- I'll fix it. Just give us a minute.

43:46.358 --> 43:49.826
Norman! Help!

43:49.828 --> 43:52.662
Norman!

43:56.368 --> 43:59.168
Oh!

43:59.170 --> 44:01.304
Oh, shite!

44:12.851 --> 44:14.917
Oh, sh...

44:41.346 --> 44:43.413
Keep your eye on that,
will you?

44:48.687 --> 44:51.754
What's on your mind, son?

44:51.756 --> 44:53.557
I've been thinking. What with?

44:54.726 --> 44:56.993
I was thinking...

44:56.995 --> 44:58.795
I could have a go
at the channel too.

44:58.797 --> 45:00.863
Yeah? Yeah.

45:00.865 --> 45:03.232
What do you think?

45:03.234 --> 45:05.201
You think you're up to it?

45:05.203 --> 45:07.437
Oh, yeah. Definitely.

45:07.439 --> 45:09.839
Yeah? Definitely.

45:21.052 --> 45:22.819
All right, rob?

45:22.821 --> 45:26.456
Evening, janine.

45:26.458 --> 45:28.991
Pint of lager, please, eight packets
of crisps... assorted flavors...

45:28.993 --> 45:31.194
no prawn cocktail,
two pork pies,

45:31.196 --> 45:33.796
three ham sandwiches
and a pint of guinness, please.

45:33.798 --> 45:36.799
I'm in training... swimming.

45:36.801 --> 45:39.268
- I've got to bulk up.
- You're swimming?

45:39.270 --> 45:42.371
Training, but I'm getting
mentally prepared.

45:42.373 --> 45:45.274
I'm in mental training.

45:45.276 --> 45:47.143
So how's things with you then?

45:47.145 --> 45:49.312
The same.

45:49.314 --> 45:51.380
How's the big fella?

45:51.382 --> 45:55.051
What? Your little boy.

45:55.053 --> 45:57.053
He fell on his arse the last
time I saw you. Oh, yeah.

45:57.055 --> 45:59.989
He's all right.
He does it all the time.

45:59.991 --> 46:01.958
He bounces back quick enough.
Oh, yeah.

46:01.960 --> 46:04.127
They're very bouncy... kids.

46:04.129 --> 46:07.797
Like balls... Or castles.

46:07.799 --> 46:10.099
Still, it's gotta be the most
difficult job in the world, that,

46:10.101 --> 46:12.201
being a dad.

46:12.203 --> 46:15.271
Probably why mine left us.

46:15.273 --> 46:17.313
But you don't Miss
what you never had, do you?

46:21.446 --> 46:24.080
Make sure you stay
in front of him, frank.

46:24.082 --> 46:25.882
If the water suddenly
gets warm,

46:25.884 --> 46:28.384
that'll be danny.

46:28.386 --> 46:30.419
How many of those
have you eaten?

46:30.421 --> 46:32.522
Oh, just the one.
Well, get rid of it.

46:35.827 --> 46:38.261
Right, okay.
Don't do anything stupid.

46:38.263 --> 46:40.096
If you get into trouble,
what do you do?

46:40.098 --> 46:42.799
Go to the boat. Yeah?

46:42.801 --> 46:45.268
All right. Now, remember,
we're not superheroes.

46:45.270 --> 46:47.270
I hear you. I'm good.
Okay, let's go.

46:47.272 --> 46:49.438
What's that?

46:49.440 --> 46:52.441
Jellyfish.

46:52.443 --> 46:54.684
They're fine. They're fine.

46:57.315 --> 47:00.149
Come on!

47:00.151 --> 47:03.252
Oh! Oh! Oh!

47:03.254 --> 47:05.288
Colder than last time.
Danny, slow down.

47:05.290 --> 47:08.558
Come on! Here we go!
Danny. Hey, danny.

47:08.560 --> 47:11.027
Watch this. Pace yourself.

47:34.919 --> 47:38.054
You are king of the jungle.

47:39.891 --> 47:42.625
I'm a lion.

47:42.627 --> 47:45.027
Now repeat after me...

48:00.645 --> 48:05.147
Right. Here you go, frank.

48:05.149 --> 48:07.583
Why can't they just hold
on to the boat and get it?

48:07.585 --> 48:10.052
Frank wants to do it right.

48:10.054 --> 48:12.054
If they touch the boat,
the swim won't count.

48:42.921 --> 48:45.388
Eddie!

48:45.390 --> 48:48.291
He's got cramps! Start the boat, chan!
Start the boat!

48:48.293 --> 48:52.461
- Danny! Danny, hold on!
- Danny!

48:52.463 --> 48:54.530
Hold on, danny!

48:56.434 --> 48:58.134
It won't start.

49:05.944 --> 49:09.578
It's okay. Calm down.
Take it easy.

49:40.511 --> 49:43.479
- What did the doctor say?
- It's fine.

49:43.481 --> 49:46.682
The doctor says he's gonna be all right.
No thanks to you.

49:46.684 --> 49:49.051
He looks to you like a dad.

49:49.053 --> 49:52.121
You should have stopped him.

49:52.123 --> 49:56.025
It wasn't frank's fault, ma. I will
not have him go in the water again.

49:56.027 --> 49:58.327
Ma, it was my own fault.

50:04.168 --> 50:06.135
I just wanted to be
the man for once.

50:08.406 --> 50:11.440
Olympic superstar.
Nike sponsorship.

50:11.442 --> 50:13.542
Just be the man, you know?

50:15.780 --> 50:17.680
Like you.

50:22.253 --> 50:26.155
I didn't want you
to be disappointed.

50:26.157 --> 50:29.557
I was when I found out it was eddie
that gave me the kiss of life.

50:33.097 --> 50:36.332
- You going training now?
- Mm.

50:36.334 --> 50:38.734
Put some down for me, will you?

50:38.736 --> 50:44.540
He can help out...
On the boat or something.

50:44.542 --> 50:47.076
But he wears a life jacket
if he's anywhere near you.

50:52.083 --> 50:55.551
So his mother's not too happy then?
I should have stopped him.

50:55.553 --> 50:59.488
Remember you stopped rob swimming in
here that time? Yeah, he was seven.

50:59.490 --> 51:02.324
He cursed like mad when I pulled him
out 'cause his mates were watching.

51:02.326 --> 51:04.593
Jumped right back in again.

51:04.595 --> 51:07.830
Oh, you know, if I had disobeyed
my father at that age,

51:07.832 --> 51:10.633
he'd have beat
the hell out of me.

51:10.635 --> 51:14.336
But I loved him.

51:14.338 --> 51:19.275
I've never hit rob... Ever.
Not once.

51:19.277 --> 51:22.411
We never can find two words
to say to each other.

51:26.084 --> 51:28.184
Seems like everything's
backwards.

51:43.401 --> 51:46.602
Why don't we just take a chance?
Go down to dover.

51:46.604 --> 51:48.704
It's a long way to go for nothing
if we don't find somebody.

51:48.706 --> 51:52.708
You said yourself, if you don't
find a pilot, you can't swim.

51:52.710 --> 51:56.812
Okay, okay, I'll go there later this week.
I'll come for the ride.

51:56.814 --> 52:00.182
Get a saver. Should be cheap enough.
Take danny too.

52:00.184 --> 52:03.886
Make sure he brings
his water wings this time.

52:13.164 --> 52:14.463
It said "apply thickly."

52:15.900 --> 52:17.533
Maybe we overdid it.

52:32.383 --> 52:35.551
I'm sorry. Oh! Was it the lorry?

52:35.553 --> 52:38.687
Mm-hmm. But he swerved first.
Lunatic.

52:38.689 --> 52:41.690
Mrs. Redmond,
you need to be more...

52:41.692 --> 52:44.212
I'll let you go one more time.

52:52.503 --> 52:54.904
There we are.

52:54.906 --> 52:58.908
Right. I've just had a word
with the barmaid.

52:58.910 --> 53:01.510
Apparently there is a guy
that can do it.

53:01.512 --> 53:03.946
Goes by the name of mad bob.

53:03.948 --> 53:07.249
Mad bob?

53:07.251 --> 53:11.220
- He doesn't sound normal.
- Oh, he sounds friggin' nuts.

53:11.222 --> 53:14.723
Is he here?
You lookin' for a boat?

53:14.725 --> 53:17.793
- We might be.
- Either you are or you're not.

53:19.463 --> 53:21.964
We are.

53:21.966 --> 53:24.687
- So it's you that's gonna be swimmin'?
- Mm-hmm.

53:31.909 --> 53:36.845
If you can't beat me, you
ain't the man to do the swim.

53:36.847 --> 53:39.415
And I ain't the man
to take you.

53:41.552 --> 53:43.872
I take it you're mad bob.

53:53.297 --> 53:55.431
We go on three.

53:57.902 --> 54:00.469
One,

54:01.572 --> 54:03.572
two,

54:03.574 --> 54:06.742
three.

54:06.744 --> 54:10.746
850 the crossing, 200 hundred
deposit, no refunds.

54:10.748 --> 54:13.482
But we get to see your boat?

54:13.484 --> 54:17.386
- What for?
- We get to see the boat.

54:17.388 --> 54:19.308
Righty-ho,
you get to see the boat.

54:22.493 --> 54:24.860
Shark, 35-footer.

54:31.569 --> 54:34.403
Fell off my bike, two-wheeler.

54:34.405 --> 54:36.705
Let's go.

54:39.510 --> 54:40.976
There she is.

54:43.781 --> 54:45.848
Is this yours?

54:48.319 --> 54:50.953
It's all right.

54:50.955 --> 54:56.458
It's good. Yeah, very nice.

54:56.460 --> 54:58.827
- There you go, fellas, tea's up.
- What date is it today?

54:58.829 --> 55:01.063
