56:53.411 --> 56:54.943
What?

56:57.915 --> 56:59.955
I'm gonna get some jelly
before it's all gone.

57:08.592 --> 57:11.026
You can have another go,
can't you?

57:11.028 --> 57:13.929
I just can't seem
to concentrate lately.

57:13.931 --> 57:18.000
You told him at last then? No, it's not that.
It's something else.

57:19.770 --> 57:22.250
I think he might be
having an affair.

57:25.643 --> 57:27.876
But he's acting so odd.

57:27.878 --> 57:29.978
I'm sorry.
That's just daft. I mean...

57:29.980 --> 57:32.681
well, there's vera.

57:32.683 --> 57:35.451
It's not funny.
She rang last week and...

57:35.453 --> 57:38.120
it's probably just got something
to do with the boat.

57:38.122 --> 57:40.756
- What boat?
- The boat.

57:40.758 --> 57:44.193
The lads are borrowin' a boat
to help frank swim the channel.

57:44.195 --> 57:46.094
What channel?

57:47.531 --> 57:49.631
Thank you.

58:17.561 --> 58:20.095
Nice. Mm.

58:23.767 --> 58:26.935
You know, we were talking
about buying a car.

58:26.937 --> 58:30.973
Mm. I fixed
the wing mirror back on.

58:30.975 --> 58:36.011
Well, michelle says arthur hall
is selling his metro. It's red.

58:36.013 --> 58:39.453
I thought we said a new car could wait?
No, we didn't. You did.

58:40.618 --> 58:43.652
We have to be careful
with the money from now on.

58:43.654 --> 58:46.622
Michelle says the insides
are just like new.

58:49.593 --> 58:51.593
She also says you've been
borrowing merv's boat...

58:51.595 --> 58:54.196
To help you train
to swim the channel.

58:54.198 --> 58:57.478
The english channel. And I was wondering
when you were thinking about telling me.

59:04.308 --> 59:08.043
I was also wondering how it is
we can't afford a new car,

59:08.045 --> 59:11.286
but you can afford to pay for a boat
to show you the way to bloody france.

59:15.185 --> 59:18.745
I'd be worried about you trying to swim all
that way, frank, if I wasn't so angry.

59:23.727 --> 59:26.194
I've never asked you
for anything, frank,

59:26.196 --> 59:28.764
but honesty was something
I took for granted.

01:00:20.918 --> 01:00:23.952
Well, look who it is,
three wise monkeys.

01:00:23.954 --> 01:00:27.255
Hey, rob, your dad's just got
a few more lengths to do.

01:00:27.257 --> 01:00:29.825
Why don't we wait for him outside?
I know about his little secret.

01:00:29.827 --> 01:00:31.393
I just wanna talk to him. Is that all right?
No, no, no, come on.

01:00:31.395 --> 01:00:33.195
- Eddie...
- Hey! Hey!

01:00:40.004 --> 01:00:43.205
You're a liar, dad.

01:00:43.207 --> 01:00:46.008
You lied to me
about swimming the channel.

01:00:48.245 --> 01:00:50.178
Maybe I did.

01:00:50.180 --> 01:00:52.414
Why?

01:00:55.252 --> 01:00:58.787
Is it because I don't have a job?
It's not about you.

01:00:58.789 --> 01:01:01.690
Because I look after the twins?
I'm not ashamed of that, dad!

01:01:01.692 --> 01:01:04.226
I'm not ashamed
like you think I should be!

01:01:04.228 --> 01:01:06.662
Good! You're not ashamed!

01:01:06.664 --> 01:01:09.765
No, but you are.

01:01:11.135 --> 01:01:14.436
You're the one who's ashamed!

01:01:14.438 --> 01:01:18.807
I'm not listening to this. Why? What
are you afraid of? Afraid I'll drown?

01:01:18.809 --> 01:01:21.777
Look at me, I'm drowning!

01:01:26.917 --> 01:01:30.819
Thirty-six years!
Thirty-six years!

01:01:30.821 --> 01:01:33.822
Twelve hours a day,
five days a week!

01:01:33.824 --> 01:01:37.426
Now you tell me, when was I
supposed to go shopping!

01:02:18.936 --> 01:02:21.970
He'll be okay.
Just needs time to cool off.

01:02:21.972 --> 01:02:24.106
We need to make sure
you keep up the times tomorrow.

01:02:24.108 --> 01:02:26.208
No. What?

01:02:26.210 --> 01:02:28.110
No.

01:02:36.487 --> 01:02:38.153
- I can't do it.
- But, frank...

01:02:38.155 --> 01:02:40.422
I can't do it.

01:02:40.424 --> 01:02:44.192
He's right. Come on,
frank, come on.

01:02:44.194 --> 01:02:46.228
I'm not going to be swimming.

01:03:12.289 --> 01:03:14.823
Your father didn't mean
to hurt you.

01:03:19.096 --> 01:03:20.862
I was married once.

01:03:24.535 --> 01:03:27.035
Her name was bridget.

01:03:27.037 --> 01:03:29.271
She left me for a jam salesman.

01:03:31.275 --> 01:03:33.542
She never even liked jam.

01:03:38.048 --> 01:03:41.016
I didn't bother
with women again after that.

01:03:41.018 --> 01:03:44.252
I was always too scared the same
thing would happen all over.

01:03:44.254 --> 01:03:49.057
If anyone tried to get close,
I just pushed them away.

01:03:52.563 --> 01:03:57.065
Your father did the same thing with you
after the accident, pushed you away.

01:03:59.937 --> 01:04:02.871
He blames me.

01:04:02.873 --> 01:04:06.608
No, he doesn't. He blames himself.
Always has.

01:04:12.216 --> 01:04:14.950
Now you're soakin' the seat,
and it's leather. It'll stain.

01:05:05.502 --> 01:05:07.936
All that way, frank.

01:05:18.048 --> 01:05:20.088
I thought we were
too old for secrets.

01:05:24.354 --> 01:05:26.421
Like learning
how to drive a bus?

01:05:38.936 --> 01:05:42.671
There was an ad in the paper.

01:05:42.673 --> 01:05:45.273
I failed twice.

01:05:47.177 --> 01:05:50.078
But I'm going to take it again.
I'm not givin' up.

01:06:19.076 --> 01:06:22.711
Let's just play when it smashes.

01:06:22.713 --> 01:06:24.746
All right, you ready?
You take that one, all right?

01:06:24.748 --> 01:06:27.582
One, two...

01:06:38.996 --> 01:06:41.763
We're not catching
the train, james.

01:06:41.765 --> 01:06:45.533
There's no point in racing.
I've got the keys, remember.

01:06:49.439 --> 01:06:51.673
- Pappy.
- Shh.

01:06:54.044 --> 01:06:57.145
- Are you playing a game?
- Yeah.

01:06:57.147 --> 01:06:58.613
Don't make me come back out.

01:06:58.615 --> 01:07:00.415
You better go inside.

01:07:04.788 --> 01:07:07.389
Is it a secret? Yeah.

01:07:07.391 --> 01:07:09.190
Like daddy's wee brother?

01:07:11.428 --> 01:07:15.397
He says we mustn't talk about
him, that it makes you sad.

01:07:15.399 --> 01:07:17.365
Does it make you sad?

01:07:18.668 --> 01:07:20.535
Sometimes.

01:07:22.806 --> 01:07:25.640
- I won't tell.
- Good boy.

01:07:29.546 --> 01:07:31.747
Are you going to
swim the channel?

01:07:33.383 --> 01:07:36.084
I don't know.
What do you think?

01:07:36.086 --> 01:07:37.752
Dad says it's too dangerous.

01:07:41.691 --> 01:07:43.825
What is the channel?

01:07:43.827 --> 01:07:48.229
It's the sea
between england and france.

01:07:48.231 --> 01:07:52.233
Are there any sharks?

01:07:52.235 --> 01:07:54.402
No sharks.

01:07:54.404 --> 01:07:57.472
- Crocodiles?
- Mm-mm.

01:07:57.474 --> 01:07:59.741
- Piranhas?
- Bananas?

01:07:59.743 --> 01:08:02.744
- Piranhas.
- Piranhas.

01:08:02.746 --> 01:08:05.613
No, no piranhas.

01:08:05.615 --> 01:08:08.349
It doesn't sound
too dangerous to me then.

01:08:08.351 --> 01:08:10.151
I'll count to five.

01:08:20.863 --> 01:08:22.796
I can swim like a fish.

01:08:34.277 --> 01:08:36.917
Are you stopping out here all day,
or are you planning to come in?

01:09:11.881 --> 01:09:14.282
Hey, big man, you not swimmin'?

01:09:40.176 --> 01:09:42.477
Yes!

01:09:46.683 --> 01:09:49.850
That's five pounds you owe me.
I told you he'd be here.

01:09:54.958 --> 01:09:56.824
We're a delegation.

01:09:58.361 --> 01:10:00.962
A delegation?

01:10:00.964 --> 01:10:04.399
It's a kind of a gang.
Thanks for that, danny.

01:10:07.871 --> 01:10:10.238
Does the delegation
have a proposal?

01:10:10.240 --> 01:10:13.975
Yeah. We think
you're wrong to give up.

01:10:13.977 --> 01:10:17.946
Now we've come this far.

01:10:17.948 --> 01:10:21.416
We also think you are a big daft
bollocks for giving... you see that?

01:10:21.418 --> 01:10:23.619
See that little lad
with red hair?

01:10:26.323 --> 01:10:29.224
It takes everything out of him
just to swim one width. Just one.

01:10:31.261 --> 01:10:33.394
He won't take any help,

01:10:33.396 --> 01:10:36.998
and he never gives up... Ever.

01:10:42.539 --> 01:10:45.220
And when he gets to
the other side... yes!

01:10:48.778 --> 01:10:50.612
I'm not givin' up.

01:11:11.601 --> 01:11:13.121
That toilet
needs cleaning again.

01:11:19.809 --> 01:11:22.443
Do it yourself.

01:11:36.693 --> 01:11:39.427
Take it steady.

01:11:39.429 --> 01:11:42.330
All right, ladies? Pam.

01:11:42.332 --> 01:11:44.799
- Oh, my god!
- All right, love.

01:11:44.801 --> 01:11:46.734
Nearly finished?

01:11:48.338 --> 01:11:50.818
Only I thought we might go out.

01:11:51.608 --> 01:11:53.074
You mean together?

01:11:57.814 --> 01:12:02.083
Oh, aye. You and me.
Me and you.

01:12:09.793 --> 01:12:12.560
Excuse me.

01:12:12.562 --> 01:12:15.096
Please don't drop the bags.
They split.

01:12:16.433 --> 01:12:18.866
Oh, aye.

01:12:18.868 --> 01:12:20.735
Sorry, pal.

01:12:26.476 --> 01:12:29.944
- See you wednesday.
- See you wednesday.

01:12:43.660 --> 01:12:45.993
I nearly drowned. We heard.

01:12:45.995 --> 01:12:49.464
In the sea? What were
you doing in the sea?

01:12:49.466 --> 01:12:53.000
I don't know.
Do you wanna go out with me?

01:12:56.005 --> 01:12:59.407
- Yeah.
- Good.

01:12:59.409 --> 01:13:01.008
That's good.

01:13:02.512 --> 01:13:05.012
Happy days.

01:13:22.165 --> 01:13:24.866
You smell of chlorine.

01:13:24.868 --> 01:13:26.908
Like dad when he was laid out.

01:13:30.907 --> 01:13:34.609
He used to smell of oil
and woodbines.

01:13:37.180 --> 01:13:41.115
I was 16.

01:13:41.117 --> 01:13:43.117
You came down to talk to dad
about something.

01:13:45.188 --> 01:13:47.054
I couldn't believe
how handsome you were.

01:13:57.200 --> 01:14:00.601
I'm learning to drive a bus.

01:14:00.603 --> 01:14:04.739
And then, if I pass,
I'm going to drive a bus.

01:14:04.741 --> 01:14:08.142
It'll be my job. A proper job.

01:14:08.144 --> 01:14:10.044
Driving a bus.

01:14:12.782 --> 01:14:14.615
I'm going up.

01:14:16.619 --> 01:14:19.520
So should you.
You have a big day tomorrow.

01:14:59.262 --> 01:15:01.662
Thanks for the sandwiches.

01:15:01.664 --> 01:15:04.232
Good luck.

01:15:04.234 --> 01:15:09.070
That, uh, time...
When I came to see your father,

01:15:09.072 --> 01:15:10.938
I didn't.

01:15:13.142 --> 01:15:15.643
I came to see you.

01:15:23.720 --> 01:15:26.554
I spy with my little eye, something beginning with...
you'll never get this... "a."

01:15:26.556 --> 01:15:28.623
Air freshener. No.

01:15:28.625 --> 01:15:30.992
Ambulance.
No. You may get it, norman.

01:15:30.994 --> 01:15:33.294
Why? 'Cause you're nearer it.

01:15:33.296 --> 01:15:35.930
You could say you're on it.
I'm on it?

01:15:35.932 --> 01:15:37.832
Kind of. Arse.

01:15:37.834 --> 01:15:41.235
No. 'Cause you'd have that as well,
unless it was norman's arse.

01:15:41.237 --> 01:15:44.305
- Leave my arse out of this.
- And that would be n-a.

01:16:30.853 --> 01:16:33.588
You okay with heights?

01:16:33.590 --> 01:16:36.290
Yeah. You?

01:16:36.292 --> 01:16:38.292
Oh, yeah. You sure?

01:16:38.294 --> 01:16:40.861
Mm-hmm.

01:16:43.733 --> 01:16:46.033
I was thinking about joan.

01:16:46.035 --> 01:16:47.935
I should have told her.

01:16:49.238 --> 01:16:50.972
Don't know what I was hiding.

01:16:54.010 --> 01:16:56.744
- Maybe we should leave him alone.
- Why?

01:16:56.746 --> 01:16:59.146
- We should be there for him.
- What if he doesn't want us there?

01:16:59.148 --> 01:17:01.716
Oh, you're as pigheaded
as your father.

01:17:01.718 --> 01:17:04.919
Of course he wants us there.
He just doesn't know how to ask.

01:17:04.921 --> 01:17:07.221
But he's not going to
achieve anything by it.

01:17:07.223 --> 01:17:10.658
How do you know?

01:17:10.660 --> 01:17:13.660
Because he's not going to bring
stuart back by swimming the channel.

01:17:14.030 --> 01:17:17.198
Oh, rob.

01:17:17.200 --> 01:17:19.934
It's not stuart he wants back.

01:17:23.339 --> 01:17:25.706
I'm away.

01:17:32.649 --> 01:17:34.715
Mom, thanks for the toys.

01:17:34.717 --> 01:17:36.384
Oh, it's okay.

01:17:38.655 --> 01:17:40.655
What toys?

01:17:48.297 --> 01:17:51.032
Better out than in, right?

01:17:51.034 --> 01:17:54.035
For god's sake.

01:17:54.037 --> 01:17:56.137
One more of them
and you're sleeping in the car.

01:18:00.009 --> 01:18:03.878
I knew a guy once...
Could fart in german.

01:18:16.893 --> 01:18:19.860
You took your time.

01:18:19.862 --> 01:18:21.429
I'm sittin' in the front.

01:18:27.937 --> 01:18:29.737
The observer fellow
seems all right.

01:18:38.848 --> 01:18:41.482
Right, it's 5:00. Let's get crackin'.
Okay, don't forget.

01:18:41.484 --> 01:18:45.419
Don't touch the boat or anyone on it once you
get going, or it will invalidate your swim.

01:18:45.421 --> 01:18:48.089
When you get to france,
get all the way onto dry land,

01:18:48.091 --> 01:18:50.291
pick up a stone
and bring it back to the boat.

01:18:50.293 --> 01:18:53.327
- Okay.
- Good luck.

01:18:53.329 --> 01:18:58.032
Thank you. Thank you. Well, go.

01:18:58.034 --> 01:18:59.800
Good luck, mate.
Good luck, frank.

01:18:59.802 --> 01:19:01.969
Thanks, lads.

01:19:01.971 --> 01:19:03.037
Right.

01:19:07.877 --> 01:19:10.778
- See youse.
- You're not joining us?

01:19:10.780 --> 01:19:14.815
No, I don't float very well.
Me neither.

01:19:17.787 --> 01:19:19.487
Okay.

01:20:22.852 --> 01:20:26.520
Come on, frank! That's the way!

01:21:14.070 --> 01:21:16.971
Ah, we'll be there
in no time, frank.

01:21:19.442 --> 01:21:22.376
The right and the left.

01:21:22.378 --> 01:21:27.214
One, two, three, four! Oh!

01:21:27.216 --> 01:21:30.484
I'm all right, frank.
I'm all right. Carry on.

01:21:33.422 --> 01:21:36.190
You passed, didn't you?

01:21:36.192 --> 01:21:39.560
I thought you'd never ask.
Well done, mom.

01:21:39.562 --> 01:21:42.296
Congratulations.
That's brilliant.

01:21:42.298 --> 01:21:45.738
Well, I think we should
celebrate with a gumdrop.

01:22:04.020 --> 01:22:06.520
- The fumes are killing me.
- I can't help that.

01:22:08.691 --> 01:22:11.392
I'm keeping this close
to keep you on course.

01:22:13.429 --> 01:22:16.196
I can't breathe!

01:22:16.198 --> 01:22:19.198
- I'll go ahead.
- Well, what bloody use will I be then?

01:22:21.037 --> 01:22:23.537
Stupid bastard. Bloody fool!

01:22:32.081 --> 01:22:34.581
I am confident.

01:22:34.583 --> 01:22:38.319
I am confident. I am a lion.

01:22:38.321 --> 01:22:40.254
I am a lion.
I'm not a timorous beastie.

01:22:41.457 --> 01:22:44.491
I'm a lion!

01:23:02.078 --> 01:23:04.545
He's doing great, isn't he?

01:23:04.547 --> 01:23:08.382
No, he's not. At this rate, he's not gonna
make it to the cap before the ebb tide.

01:23:08.384 --> 01:23:10.751
And if he doesn't, he's gonna
get swept back out to sea.

01:23:10.753 --> 01:23:13.253
Isn't that being a bit bleak?
No, he's right.

01:23:13.255 --> 01:23:16.357
Look, I'll pick up the pace
and he's gonna have to keep up.

01:23:16.359 --> 01:23:18.158
- Bloody hell.
- Better do some hypothermia checks.

01:23:18.160 --> 01:23:19.593
Can we get closer to him?

01:23:24.433 --> 01:23:27.134
Frank, where are you
swimming from?

01:23:27.136 --> 01:23:30.070
England.

01:23:30.072 --> 01:23:33.707
- Where in england?
- Dover.

01:23:33.709 --> 01:23:36.710
- What day is it?
- What?

01:23:36.712 --> 01:23:40.714
- What day is it?
- Thursday.

01:23:40.716 --> 01:23:43.283
He seems all right.

01:23:54.663 --> 01:23:58.165
Come on.

01:23:58.167 --> 01:24:01.702
I didn't think to ask where
in france he was swimming to.

01:24:01.704 --> 01:24:04.338
There, that's where
he's swimming to.

01:24:04.340 --> 01:24:06.507
- How do you know?
- Pappy showed me.

01:24:06.509 --> 01:24:09.276
- When did pappy show you?
- I'm not telling you.

01:24:14.550 --> 01:24:16.650
How many times
did you try it yourself?

01:24:16.652 --> 01:24:19.753
Three. Did you ever make it?

01:24:19.755 --> 01:24:21.555
Third time lucky.

01:24:34.403 --> 01:24:36.684
There it is, sortie, way out.

01:24:57.693 --> 01:25:01.428
What is it? Ebb tide.

01:25:01.430 --> 01:25:05.099
- It's dragging him back out.
- What if he can't beat it?

01:25:05.101 --> 01:25:08.235
Can't we do anything?

01:25:08.237 --> 01:25:11.605
- He's in for the long haul.
- He won't be able to last that long.

01:25:11.607 --> 01:25:15.242
Yes, he will. He won't. His
body temperature is dropping.

01:25:15.244 --> 01:25:17.804
If he doesn't make this beach,
he's not gonna make it at all.

01:25:18.747 --> 01:25:23.450
Frank! You've only three miles
to go, frank!

01:25:23.452 --> 01:25:26.753
I know you're hurtin', but you gotta swim
faster, frank. The tide's against you.

01:25:26.755 --> 01:25:29.690
Frank, you gotta swim faster.
Come on!

01:25:36.332 --> 01:25:39.299
You can do it, frank.

01:25:39.301 --> 01:25:41.135
You can do it.

01:26:10.332 --> 01:26:13.212
Stay there. Stay there. Don't move!
Don't you move from there!

01:26:21.377 --> 01:26:23.911
Stop that.

01:26:25.781 --> 01:26:28.215
Stop it.

01:26:41.363 --> 01:26:43.564
Come on, frank, come on.

01:27:22.771 --> 01:27:24.838
Is he all right?

01:27:24.840 --> 01:27:28.008
No!

01:27:33.549 --> 01:27:35.582
Bloody hell.

01:27:53.302 --> 01:27:55.736
I need to come out, lads.

01:27:57.339 --> 01:27:59.706
What do you think you're doing?

01:27:59.708 --> 01:28:03.043
Why don't you just take it slower
for a wee while. See if it passes.

01:28:03.045 --> 01:28:07.781
I'm sorry, chan.
I can't do it, mate.

01:28:07.783 --> 01:28:11.518
- You're nearly there. Look, it's not far.
- I can't do it.

01:28:11.520 --> 01:28:14.821
Frank, your body's hurting because
you're beginning to burn fat.

01:28:14.823 --> 01:28:17.491
It won't last though. Carry on,
you'll get through it. Yeah, frank.

01:28:17.493 --> 01:28:20.394
It's just a pain barrier.
It's all in your mind.

01:28:20.396 --> 01:28:23.730
- Get me out. It's too far.
- Bollocks. It's always been this far.

01:28:23.732 --> 01:28:27.634
- You come in and swim it then!
- Fine. Get on board, we can all go home.

01:28:27.636 --> 01:28:32.439
All my life I've looked up
to you, frank. All my life.

01:28:32.441 --> 01:28:35.642
I never saw you back down from anything.
It's too far.

01:28:35.644 --> 01:28:38.879
I'm nobody, me, I know that.

01:28:38.881 --> 01:28:43.383
But I'm not daft.
I see what's going on here.

01:28:43.385 --> 01:28:45.319
Out here
in the middle of nowhere.

01:28:48.357 --> 01:28:50.717
But he's not here,
is he, frank?

01:28:51.760 --> 01:28:53.794
He never was.

01:28:55.698 --> 01:28:58.018
It's taken you 23 years
to find that out.

01:29:02.938 --> 01:29:05.105
So what now?

01:29:07.443 --> 01:29:08.975
Well, I'll tell you what now.

01:29:11.513 --> 01:29:14.948
You get back to swimming, and you
shut up about how far it is.

